  "prompt": "What is the average salary of an MBA graduate in India?",
  "response": "The average salary of an MBA graduate in India varies depending on factors like specialization, college reputation, work experience, and industry. Generally, the average salary ranges from:\n\n1. Entry-level (0-2 years experience):\n- Average: \u20b94-8 lakhs per annum\n- Top B-schools: \u20b910-15 lakhs per annum\n\n2. Mid-level (3-5 years experience):\n- Average: \u20b98-15 lakhs per annum\n- Top performers: \u20b915-25 lakhs per annum\n\n3. Specialized domains:\n- Finance: \u20b96-12 lakhs\n- Marketing: \u20b95-10 lakhs\n- IT/Technology: \u20b97-15 lakhs\n- Consulting: \u20b98-20 lakhs\n\n4. Top B-schools (IIMs, XLRI):\n- Placement packages can range from \u20b920-30 lakhs\n- Some exceptional packages exceed \u20b940 lakhs\n\n5. Factors affecting salary:\n- College reputation\n- Academic performance\n- Prior work experience\n- Internship achievements\n- Interview performance\n\nThese figures are approximate and can change based on individual circumstances and market conditions.",
